results.name: Concatenation of the two divisors of a semiprime, smallest divisor first.
comment: Concatenation of the divisors starting with the largest one leads to another sequence.
link: Michael De Vlieger, Table of n, a(n) for n = 1..10000
mathematica: FromDigits@ Flatten[IntegerDigits@ Table[#1, {#2}] & @@@ FactorInteger@ #] & /@ Select[Range@ 144, PrimeOmega@ # == 2 &] (* _Michael De Vlieger_, Oct 01 2015 *)
program: (PARI) do(x)=my(v=List()); forprime(p=2, sqrt(x), forprime(q=p, x\p, listput(v, [p*q, eval(Str(p, q))]))); Vec(apply(u->u[2], vecsort(v, 1))) \\ _Charles R Greathouse IV_, Sep 30 2015
